                "type": "output_text",
                "text": "Here are the latest updates for London Underground services:\n\n1. **General Status**: Most lines are running as usual, but there are minor disruptions affecting the District and Elizabeth lines due to faulty trains and planned maintenance. The Northern line has partial closures with replacement bus services in operation.\n\n2. **Planned Maintenance**: There are scheduled track closures between Saturday 13 December and Sunday 14 December on the Northern line between Hampstead and Edgware, and Golders Green and Edgware [TfL Status Updates](https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status).\n\n3. **Christmas and New Year Services**: No Tube services will run on Christmas Day, and there will be early finishes on Christmas Eve. Overnight services will be available on New Year’s Eve, with some stations possibly closing temporarily to manage crowds [Transport for London](https://tfl-newsroom.prgloo.com/news/majority-of-tfl-services-running-over-christmas-and-new-year-to-help-customers-make-the-most-of-london-this-festive-season).\n\nCheck the [Transport for London website](https://tfl.gov.uk/tube-dlr-overground/status) for real-time updates and detailed service changes.",
